{
  "stem": "8784.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the other possibility would have been that sometime later on, while we were in Brunnlitz and some of the lost railroad cars that Schindler brought into his own camp-- that maybe there was a David Urbach that came, and it was that transport.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it somehow has a ring of possibility that this Urbach arrived together with us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But nevertheless, I did not know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Anxiety and fear combined and the lack of rationality by then-- I had no idea that another Urbach was called.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "After all these names were called-- and the best I can figure out, there were 700 people-- we were loaded on cattle cars, and Gross Rosen again, and shipped out from Gross Rosen.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And again, I-- I have to stress that I had no idea what this list is all about.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Nobody told us at that time that this is a list that Oskar Schindler has created and that this is a list that will take us to Oskar Schindler's factory.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was just not known to me at the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But nevertheless, we were shipped out of this concentration camp, and there was some joy in the fact that we were leaving this concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "What the future held for us, we didn't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But nevertheless, we were happy that we were leaving this camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Unbeknownst to us, Oskar Schindler did pull off a scheme and has received a linen factory that the Germans gave to him in the town of Brunnlitz.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he promises the German authorities that he will convert this linen factory into a pots and pans and into a-- something that makes cartridges for the rockets, and this will be a vital industry.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
